title: George H. W. Bush
added: At the elite level, a number of commentators and political experts deplored the state of American politics in 1991-1992, and reported the voters were angry. Many analysts blamed the poor quality of national election campaigns.<ref>Gil Troy,  "Stumping in the bookstores: A literary history of the 1992 presidential campaign." ''Presidential Studies Quarterly'' (1995): 697-710. [https://www.jstor.org/stable/27551506 online]</ref>
